        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 19 at 4:48PM EDT until June 19 at 5:15PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 448 PM EDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from Kells Corner to Chase City to near Clarksville, moving
east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to trees and powerlines.

These severe storms will be near...
Boydton around 455 PM EDT.
South Hill around 510 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by these severe thunderstorms include Gary,
Nelson, Wilburn, Spanish Grove, Beechwood, North View, Finchley, John
H Kerr Dam, Finneywood, and Skipwith.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
